      "settings": {
        "heading": "Timber love & care",
        "content": "<p>All our furniture is built from the strongest of reclaimed timber that’s formed the structural heart of Britain’s oldest buildings for hundreds of years. But every British classic needs ongoing TLC (Timber Love & Care). Here’s how to give them just that:</p>",
        "alignment": "center"
      }
    },
    "1ef29464-1435-472e-ba84-3bd078ae1790": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "2df4f4d4-108e-4949-858a-036da9ce26ad": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I put drinks/hot plates on my furniture?",
            "answer": "We recommend that you use table mats and coasters."
          }
        },
        "b7dafeb1-c89f-4c9c-914c-69b71a057099": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What do you suggest for day to day upkeep?",
            "answer": "You can use a slightly damp (almost dry) cloth, please do not use any silicone based products, all-purpose cleaning sprays or other chemicals that can stain or strip wood."
          }
        },
        "d7c3b55c-cb6f-47d2-b4ad-2dd11aa39d2d": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will my furniture crack or split?",
            "answer": "If small cracks appear on the surface, this is quite normal and nothing to be worried about – your furniture is not faulty/damaged, it is all part of the character of reclaimed wood. Wood is a natural product and it ‘moves’ which is also known as reaching its equilibrium or simply a case of being clever in a bid to acclimatise to the environment/room temperature that is it in.If cracks do appear, it is a reminder or a good indicationthat it is ‘wax time’."
          }
        },
        "e93e5130-abe9-4423-b83d-afb3095acf5f": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do I stop my furniture from fading in colour?",
            "answer": "Avoid placing your furniture in direct sunlight as the UV rays from the sun can fade the wood. To keep your furniture looking beautiful, we recommend regular waxing, as this with maintain the protection and colour/overall appearance."
          }
        },
        "1c80a7c1-d608-4dc1-b6d0-a0ab0ec0ab8b": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens if there are any food or drink spillages on my furniture?",
            "answer": "We recommend that you remove any food or drink spillages immediately. Please contact us if you have any specific concerns and we'll be happy to chat through it with you."
          }
        }
      },
